  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bca\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Three names were proposed for the presidency",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The names of three members of Parliament to fill the vacant post of President following the resignation of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa were proposed in Parliament today (19).",
        "Accordingly, the names of Acting President and Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe, Member of Parliament Dalus Alagaperuma and Member of Parliament Anurakumara Dissanayake were proposed.",
        "Leader of Opposition Sajith Premadasa proposed the name of Member of Parliament Dulles Alagaperuma and Member of Parliament (Professor) Honorable G.L. Peiris suggested it.",
        "Ranil Wickramasinghe's name was proposed by Speaker of Parliament and Minister Dinesh Gunawardena, and Member of Parliament Manusha Nanayakkara seconded it.",
        "Similarly, the name of Member of Parliament Hon'ble Anurakumara Dissanayake was proposed by Member of Parliament Hon'ble Vijitha Herath and Member of Parliament (Finance) Harini Amarasuriya seconded it.",
        "Parliamentary Secretary Thammika Dasanayake announced that the nominations of these three candidates have been accepted for the next presidential post under the Presidential Elections (Special Elections) Act No. 2 of 1981.",
        "Accordingly, tomorrow (20) one of these three will be elected as the next president by the votes of the members of parliament.",
        "The former President had sent his resignation letter to the Speaker on the 14th. Accordingly, on the 16th, the Parliament was convened and the Secretary General of the Parliament informed the Parliament that there was a vacancy in the post of President and it was announced that nominations from the members of Parliament would be accepted to fill the vacancy. Accordingly today (19) the nominations for the post of President were accepted."
      ],
